Sometimes referred to as Panopticon/Wheels Within Wheels due to the artists participating in the split; it is unclear if "It's Later Than You Think" is intended to be an official title. 1. Panopticon - ...speaking...(collapsed version) - 10:40 2. Panopticon - The Ghosts of Haymarket Square - 7:28 3. Wheels Within Wheels - begining - 4:45 4. Wheels Within Wheels - White Light Rains Down On.... Track #1 is an acoustic re-recording of a song from Panopticon. Track #2 is about the Haymarket massacre and is dedicated to the Haymarket martyrs, who were executed by the state for a bomb-throwing for which even the state admitted they were not culpable. A few of those sentenced were pardoned by Governor John Peter Altgeld; his political career ended as a result. Read more on Last.fm.
